 images (2006) J Geophys Res, 111, pp. G04002; Smith, L., Sheng, Y., MacDonald, G., Hinzman, L., Disappearing Arctic lakes (2005) Science, 308, pp. 1429-1429; Bonan, G.B., Levis, S., Quantifying carbon-nitrogen feedbacks in the Community Land Model (CLM4) (2010) Geophys Res Lett, 37, pp. L07401; Zaehle, S., Friedlingstein, P., Friend, A.D., Terrestrial nitrogen feedbacks (2010) Geophys Res Lett, 37, pp. L01401. , may accelerate future climate change; Waelbroeck, C., Monfray, P., Oechel, W., Hastings, S., Vourlitis, G., The impact of permafrost thawing on the carbon dynamics of tundra (1997) Geophys Res Lett, 24, pp. 229-232; Mack, M.C., Schuur, E.A.G., Bret-Harte, M.S., Shaver, G.R., Chapin III, F.S., Ecosystem carbon storage in arctic tundra reduce by long-term nutrient fertilization (2004) Nature, 431 (7007), pp. 440-443. , DOI 10.1038/nature02887; Euskirchen, E., McGuire, A., Chapin III, F., Yi, S., Thompson, C., Changes in vegetation in northern Alaska under scenarios of climate change, 2003-2100: Implications for climate feedbacks (2009) Ecol Appl, 19, pp. 1022-1043; Carrasco, J.J., Neff, J.C., Harden, J.W., Modeling physical and biogeochemical controls over carbon accumulation in a boreal forest soil (2006) J Geophys Res (Biogeosci), 111, pp. G02004; Bohn, T.J., Lettenmaier, D.P., Systematic biases in large-scale estimates of wetland methane emissions arising from water table formulations (2010) Geophys Res Lett, 37, pp. L22401; Van Huissteden, J., Methane emissions from permafrost thaw lakes limited by lake drainage (2011) Nat Clim, 1, pp. 119-123; Ise, T., Dunn, A.L., Wofsy, S.C., Moorcroft, P.R., High sensitivity of peat decomposition to climate change through water-table feedback (2008) Nat Geosci, 1, pp. 763-766; Matthews, H.D., Eby, M., Ewen, T., Friedlingstein, P., Hawkins, B.J., What determines the magnitude of carbon cycle-climate feedbacks? (2007) Global Biogeochem Cycles, 21, pp. GB2012; Friedlingstein, P., Dufresne, J.-L., Cox, P.M., Rayner, P., Ho